 13  /-!
 14  # monoid and group homomorphisms
 15  
 16  This file defines the basic structures for monoid and group
 17  homomorphisms, both unbundled (e.g. `is_monoid_hom f`) and bundled
 18  (e.g. `monoid_hom M N`, a.k.a. `M →* N`). The unbundled ones are deprecated
 19  and the plan is to slowly remove them from mathlib.
 20  
 21  ## main definitions
 22  
 23  monoid_hom, is_monoid_hom (deprecated), is_group_hom (deprecated)
 24  
 25  ## Notations
 26  
 27  →* for bundled monoid homs (also use for group homs)
 28  →+ for bundled add_monoid homs (also use for add_group homs)
 29  
 30  ## implementation notes
 31  
 32  There's a coercion from bundled homs to fun, and the canonical
 33  notation is to use the bundled hom as a function via this coercion.
 34  
 35  There is no `group_hom` -- the idea is that `monoid_hom` is used.
 36  The constructor for `monoid_hom` needs a proof of `map_one` as well
 37  as `map_mul`; a separate constructor `monoid_hom.mk'` will construct
 38  group homs (i.e. monoid homs between groups) given only a proof
 39  that multiplication is preserved,
 40  
 41  Throughout the `monoid_hom` section implicit `{}` brackets are often used instead of type class `[]` brackets.
 42  This is done when the instances can be inferred because they are implicit arguments to the type `monoid_hom`.
 43  When they can be inferred from the type it is faster to use this method than to use type class inference.
 44  
 45  ## Tags
 46  
 47  is_group_hom, is_monoid_hom, monoid_hom
 48  
 49  -/
 50  
 51  library_note "low priority instance on morphisms"
 52  "We have instances stating that the composition or the product of two morphisms is again a morphism.
 53  Type class inference will 'succeed' in applying these instances when they shouldn't apply (for
 54  example when the goal is just `⊢ is_mul_hom f` the instances `is_mul_hom.comp` or `is_mul_hom.mul`
 55  might still succeed). This can cause type class inference to loop.
 56  To avoid this, we make the priority of these instances very low. We should think about not making
 57  these declarations instances in the first place."
 58
